column10:
im still doing the main story and i know the endgame grind/coop is at least pretty okay, but wow dude! the storytelling and the theatrics of fights are almost as impressive as nier:automata! it does get a little bit cringe sometimes, but in a good way that reminds me about the good times i had with old jrpgs like star ocean, tales of abyss, and valkyrie profile.

edit: 
now that im done with all the endgame grind except supp v+ from curio, i can safely say this is an amazing game and has the skeleton to become a fun grinding game in the future. the most notable aspect are the different types of engaging action combat that are as fun as MHW. 

however, to me, there are few questionable designs which are:
1. frequent cutscene interrupting the flow of combat; 
2. certain item's abysmal droprate that ends up promotes afk farming somewhat similar to bitcoin mining;
3. huge difficulty and performance gap between characters due to their skill sets, especially invincibility;
4. the lack of any targetable mechanics for grinding, eg. sigils and endgame weapon/materials;
5. forced camera movement and forced simulated/smooth mouse input.
but these are only minor problems that don't really impact the experience negatively, maybe except the camera and mouse.

content/price-wise, it is about the average 7/10 in 2012's standard, which means it is probably 9/10 (or even 10) in 2024's standard. if you want to get the game for the grind, i do suggest wait for detailed roadmap or possibly updates before purchasing because the devs are known to be pretty non-responsive.

